*laditools-1.0.1-r3 (01 Dec 2013)

  01 Dec 2013; Karl Linden (lilrc) <lilrc@users.sourceforge.net>
  -laditools-1.0.1-r1.ebuild, +laditools-1.0.1-r3.ebuild,
  -laditools-9999.ebuild, laditools-9999-r1.ebuild:
  Introduce a small hack to remove wmladi no matter how the python 
  wrappings work. Thanks to Zlobin Nikita for reporting the issue.
  Removed old ebuilds.
  Update DESCRIPTION and HOMEPAGE.
  PYTHON_REQUIRED_USE in REQUIRED_USE.
  Use slots for more accurate dependencies.
  Some ordering (alphabetically).

  31 Jul 2013; Karl Linden (lilrc) <lilrc@users.sourceforge.net>
  -laditools-1.0.ebuild, -laditools-1.0_rc1.ebuild:
  Removed very old ebuilds.

*laditools-9999-r1 (31 Mar 2013)
*laditools-1.0.1-r2 (31 Mar 2013)

  31 Mar 2013; Karl Linden (lilrc) <lilrc@users.sourceforge.net>
  +laditools-1.0.1-r2.ebuild, +laditools-9999-r1.ebuild:
  Depend on the USE flags to ensure the correct implementation is used.
  Drop dependency on dev-lang/python it is handled by distutils-r1.

  26 Mar 2013; Dominique Michel <dominique_libre@users.sourceforge.net>
  -laditools-1.0.1.ebuild
  +laditools-1.0.1-r1.ebuild
  laditools-9999.rbuild, laditools-1.0.1-r1.ebuild: added missing depend for
  window maker dock app and related USE flag.
  laditools-1.0.ebuild: changed KEYWORD to ~x86 (repoman)

  29 Jan 2013; Nedko Arnaudov <nedko@arnaudov.name> laditools-1.0.ebuild:
  Make laditools-1.0 depend on wmdocklib

  wmdocklib is used by wmladi

  28 Dec 2012; Dominique Michel <dominique_libre@users.sourceforge.net>
  Import from the ladi overlay
  
  26 Dec 2012; Karl Lindén <lilrc@users.sourceforge.net>
  laditools-1.0_rc8-ebuild, laditools_1.0.1.ebuild, laditools-9999.ebuild:
  Replace deprecated python-distutils-ng with python-r1 + distutils-r1
  Fix dependency on pygobject

  09 Dec 2012; Karl Lindén <lilrc@users.sourceforge.net>
  +laditools-1.0.1.ebuild, +laditools-1.0_rc8.ebuild, laditools-9999.ebuild
  +files/laditools-1.0_rc8-rsvg.patch:
  Updated ebuilds
    Use EAPI 5
    Use python-distutils-ng instead of python and distutils
    Updated dependencies
  Updated copyright notices

  28 Dec 2008; Marc-Olivier Barre <marco@marcochapeau.org>
  laditools-9999.ebuild now depends on dev-python/pyyaml

  27 Dec 2008; Marc-Olivier Barre <marco@marcochapeau.org>
  laditools-9999.ebuild now uses the git repository
  no more pyxml dependency

  15 Dec 2008; Thomas Kuther <gimpel@sonnenkinder.org>
  +laditools-1.0_rc1.ebuild:
  initial ebuild

